Title: Row '⋮' trigger is invisible when keyboard-focused and unreachable on touch devices

Finding:
.row-menu-btn is set to opacity:0 and pointer-events:none by default and only revealed by `.browse-table tbody tr:hover .row-menu-btn` or `.row-menu-btn[aria-expanded='true']`. There is no :focus/:focus-visible rule. Consequences: (1) A keyboard user tabbing to the button gets NO visible focus indicator (the button, including any outline, is fully transparent) until they happen to activate it — violating WCAG 2.4.7 Focus Visible and 2.1.1 Keyboard. (2) On touch devices there is no :hover state at all, so the button stays opacity:0 AND pointer-events:none, meaning it cannot be tapped — the entire row-actions feature (Download/Delete/Move/Copy) is unreachable on phones/tablets, violating WCAG 2.5.1/2.5.8. The trigger must be perceivable and operable without a hover-capable pointer.

Fix instructions (follow exactly; make targeted, minimal changes):
In src/app.css, fix the .row-menu trigger so it is perceivable and operable for keyboard and touch users. Add a selector that reveals the button on keyboard focus, e.g. add `:focus-visible` (and/or `:focus-within` on the row) alongside the existing hover/aria-expanded reveal rule:

.browse-table tbody tr:hover .row-menu-btn,
.browse-table tbody tr:focus-within .row-menu-btn,
.row-menu-btn:focus-visible,
.row-menu-btn[aria-expanded='true'] {
  opacity: 1;
  pointer-events: auto;
}

